article.headline: Cent. Connecticut St. 73, Fairleigh Dickinson 60
article.story: HACKENSACK, N.J. (AP) -- Shemik Thompson scored a career-high 21 points to lead Central Connecticut State to a 73-60 win over Fairleigh Dickinson on Thursday night. Ken Horton finished with 14 points and 11 rebounds for the Blue Devils (13-14, 9-7 Northeast Conference), while Marcus Palmer came off the bench to add 14 points and nine boards and Tristan Blackwood added 12 points. Manny Ubilla scored 21 points -- including five 3-pointers- for FDU (7-18, 3-12), while Sean Baptiste finished with 17 points and seven rebounds and Bernell Murray added 16 points. The teams traded baskets early, with Central Connecticut holding a 32-31 lead at the break. The Blue Devils took command with a 20-2 run midway through the second half. Central Connecticut also won the battle of the boards, outrebounding the Knights 46-33.
